description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you caring, compassionate and committed to providing the best service possible for young people?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CNWL provides an immunisation service for children across Hillingdon, Brent and Ealing. The service is primarily be delivered through a school based model, offering all school aged vaccinations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a band 5 registered nurse with an interest in working with children. A nurse with enthusiasm, energy and a passion for delivering the best care possible and have some knowledge of the childhood immunisation schedule. You will work as part of a team to organise, plan, deliver and evaluate vaccination programmes and be expected to attend immunisation sessions at school and clinics. The role involves regular early starts. The nurse will need to be a car driver and will be required to drive to Brent, Ealing and Hillingdon Schools daily. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The immunisation team work closely with other services and key stakeholders such as (but not exclusive to); school nursing teams, child health department, GPs, Public Health England and commissioners.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In return for your commitment we will make sure you receive the support and development you need to prepare yourself for future challenges. We provide good supervision and a first class learning experience in all aspects of community immunisation. We also make it easy for you to access continuing professional development according to the needs of the Service. CNWL is recognised locally, nationally and internationally for providing high quality, innovative healthcare. We aim to employ only the best people, and our experts are frequently called upon to contribute to national health strategy and policy, and many models of our care have been adapted for use in other countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
